<messaging:emailTemplate subject="Free Goods Approval Request Notification : {!RelatedTo.Name}" recipientType="User" relatedToType="EUR_CRM_Sales_Order__c"><messaging:htmlEmailBody >    <br>Hi {!Relatedto.EUR_CRM_Manager__r.Name},</br>    <br><br>A new free goods request has been created and awaits your approval. Details are as below:</br></br>    <br><br><b>Customer Name </b>-: {!Relatedto.EUR_CRM_Account__r.Name} </br></br>    <br><br><b>Order Status</b> -: {!Relatedto.EUR_CRM_Order_Status__c} </br></br>    <br><br><b>Order Processing Notes</b> -: {!Relatedto.EUR_CRM_Notes__c} </br></br>    <br><br><b>Name of the SR who took the order</b> -: {!Relatedto.EUR_CRM_Created_By_Name__c} </br></br>    <br/>    <br/>    <c:EUR_CRM_SalesOrderItemTable soId="{!RelatedTo.Id}" />    <br/>    <!--<br><br> To approve or reject this item, click this link {!Relatedto.Link} or reply to this email with one of these words in the first line of the email message: <b>APPROVE, APPROVED, YES, REJECT, REJECTED, NO </b></br></br>-->    <br><br> To approve or reject this item, click this &nbsp;<apex:outputlink value="{!LEFT($Api.Partner_Server_URL_140,FIND('.com',$Api.Partner_Server_URL_140)+4)+relatedTo.Id}">link</apex:outputlink> or reply to this email with one of these words in the first line of the email message: <b>APPROVE, APPROVED, YES, REJECT, REJECTED, NO </b></br></br>    <br><br>If replying via email, you can also add comments on the second line. Comments will be stored with the approval request in Salesforce CRM.</br></br>    <!--<br><br>You can also approve, reject and comment on this request from your feed: {!BMCServiceDesk__Chatter_Listener__c.Link}</br></br>--></messaging:htmlEmailBody></messaging:emailTemplate>